'Cell' were a New York-based band often tagged with the label of Grunge given
the time frame of their existence, though college rock or alternative is
arguably a more apt description. The band formed in 1990 and split c.1995.
Championed by Sonic Youth's Thurston Moore, they released a 7 inch on his
Ecstatic Peace label, later signing to Geffen.
